INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(1,1,'Julius Caesar','russian','2:00:00','This is a classic tragedy of William Shakespeare translated by Mikhail Zenkevich. And this is Shakespeare beyond time and space, because this story could have been a thousand years ago, and now, and will be the same in a thousand years. The audience will see the prediction through the centuries - how the story will develop, if human vices and the thirst for eternal change are at the head of everything, and the main historical character, the people, will become only a toy in the hands of conspirators. The line between politics and pop culture is blurred.',13,4);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(2,1,'Julius Caesar','english','2:00:00','Caesar returns in triumph to Rome and the people pour out of their homes to celebrate. Alarmed by the autocrat’s popularity, the educated élite conspire to bring him down. After his assassination, civil war erupts on the streets of the capital.',27,9);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(3,1,'Julius Caesar','english','2:52:00','The assassination of Julius Caesar is the subject of this powerful drama from the pen of William Shakespeare. Brutus, the main focus of the play, is a conflicted Roman general who struggles with the decision to join a plot to kill his friend, Caesar. Exploring moral and political issues that remain relevant today, "Julius Caesar" is one of Shakespeare''s most essential and entertaining plays.',30,10);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(4,2,'Romeo and Juliet','english','3:30:00',30,10);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(5,2,'Romeo and Juliet','russian','3:10:00','The world-famous story about the love and death of lovers, about the blood feud between the two families that killed this love, told by the great William Shakespeare, acquired a universal scale in the production of the People''s artist of Russia Valery Belyakovich. The viewer will witness eternal conflicts, tragic and senseless. But the main thing — love, "the two most beautiful creatures". The energy of young enthusiasm, lyrics and tragedy in the actors play capture the viewer. A majestic music and large-scale folk scenes revive in the emotional memory of the frescoes of the middle ages.',13,3);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(6,3,'Hamlet','english','3:45:00',30,10);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(7,3,'Hamlet','russian','3:30:00','The classic plot of William Shakespeare needs no introduction. This time the production of the most famous play of the great English playwright was undertaken by the famous Director Valery Belyakovich. The philosophical aspect of the play the Director brings to the viewer in a characteristic sharp, dynamic way, actualizing the realities of modern society.',13,4);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(8,4,'Othello','english','2:55:00','The republic of Venice employs General Othello, a self-made man and a Moor, to defend its overseas territories against the Turks. As the Turkish threat gathers and Venetian forces are despatched to Cyprus, the love Othello holds for his new wife becomes a raging, uncontrollable torrent. Iago, a junior officer secretly enraged by Othello, exploits his General’s ambiguous position and ingenuous nature, driving him into a passionate and overpowering jealousy. Othello is an all too human story; marked by the domestic intimacy of a chamber piece, it has the feel of a relentless Greek tragedy. The wasteland of death may be both Iago’s goal and his harvest, but the stage belongs to Othello, a man who loved perhaps unwisely and too well.',29,9);
