INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(27,8,'Vanyushin''s Children','russian','2:20:00','The Maly theatre presents the viewer with a play by Sergei Naydenov "Children Vanyushina". Naidenov is the name of the writer Sergei Alexeev, who grew up in a merchant''s family and who knew this way of life. The characters are slightly different from the inhabitants of Zamoskvorechye in the plays of Ostrovsky — it is not the tyrants Titus Titici, and people who can think about moral and personal problems of people that surround them. The protagonist of this play is a man who has lived a long life and reflects on the fate of his children, how they will live on with him and without him. He sincerely cares about children, but, unfortunately, does not find a response in them. They are looking for their own, new ways. When the play appeared in 1901 and was made known to the provincial Director N. N. Sinelnikov law , it has attracted the attention not only of audiences (the play went on the boards for a long time), but also theater and literary critics. About heroes Naidenova talked no less than about Chekhov''s characters — Treplev, Peta Trofimov. These are young people who are looking for their way in life, they are tired of the stagnation surrounding their parents. Then it was very important. Director Vitaly Ivanov found in the play something different, consonant with our time and, above all, the situation in the country, when the institution of the family is destroyed, and many experts even argue that marriage, which existed for centuries, can disappear in its usual forms. Children stop taking care of their parents, parents stop taking care of their children. The audience will have a chance to assess the relevance of the play today.',47,3);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(28,9,'The Lower Depths','russian','3:20:00','The brilliant plays of M. Gorky along with the unique plays of Chekhov made the world fame of The art theater. The resounding success of the Gorky play "at the bottom" had no analogues in the history of the domestic theater. Man in search of the meaning of life. It is strange to look for him, living in a dirty flophouse, in poverty, in hunger. And there is whether it — happiness? Got it! You gotta believe... The man himself, his Creator, say Gorky''s heroes. But where is happiness? The play calls for reflection. The production was carried out by a talented Director, people''s artist Of Russia V. R. Belyakovich. Iron plank beds, white robes of the characters on the background of a black huge stage-all this only complements the unique images played by the best actors of the theater with all the dedication and love for people and the great Maxim Gorky.',13,3);
