INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(33,11,'The Cherry Orchard','russian','2:25:00','"The cherry orchard" at the Moscow art theatre. M. Gorky was staged in 1988 by a wonderful great artist-people''s artist of the USSR, laureate of the state prize Sergey Danchenko, artistic Director of the National academic drama theatre. I. Franco. He staged the production in spite of his personal interests and benefits, simply because of decency, talent and human dignity. For what it is with all the emotional sensitivity and understanding of the concept of the domestic genius of Anton Chekhov — recreated "the Cherry orchard" on stage, the Moscow art theatre. Mmm. Gorky, he was expelled from the Union of theatrical figures of Ukraine. For "warned"was the then leadership of the Ukrainian STD:" in the Moscow art theater. M. Gorky is not recommended to stage performances." It was a "glorious" time when Oleg Efremov divided the team into two unequal parts, leaving on Tverskoy Boulevard most of the troupe with excellent "leading and main" actors, among whom were his classmates. To the question: "where can we go?"- the answer was simple":"...I don''t care, go to the Rubber club." Among the few who dared to break the will of the "innovator"and put contrary to the order of the performances in the Moscow art theater. M. Gorky, were People''s artists of the USSR Boris Pokrovsky and Sergei Danchenko, and the third hero — Roman Viktyuk, who did not have at that time (even in the form of high rank) any protection.',13,4);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(34,11,'The Cherry Orchard','russian','2:45:00','The play is about the change of eras, which responds to pain in every heart. Generation of Ranevskaya and Gayev, old Russian nobles, sentimental and impractical leaves. They must yield to business pressure of Lopakhin. The performance is carefully preserved in the production of Igor Ilyinsky.',47,5);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(35,11,'The Cherry Orchard','russian','2:35:00','Landowner Lyubov Ranevskaya returns from Paris to her family estate, which was on the verge of ruin. The main value of this estate — a luxurious cherry orchard as a memory of family, childhood and home. Ranevskaya was not at home for more than five years, trying to get rid of the longing for an early deceased son, drowned in a pond near the estate. Because for her arrival home both happy and anxious. Everything reminds of a tragic event and foreshadows an unhappy end.',16,3);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(36,11,'The Cherry Orchard','russian','2:10:00','The immortal Chekhov''s masterpiece will always be a spectator. If the planet survives our political quest and the melting ice in Antarctica. People and then, on the remains of land, will be surprised by the stories about all the benefits of dried cherries, and learn many other absurdities of "tragic Comedy" that has become an encyclopedia of the Russian soul. In "the Cherry orchard" is all that we know, want, all, remember, all that I need... if only I knew what it was!.. If I knew!..',15,4);
