INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(46,13,'Uncle Vanya','russian','3:20:00','Vanya, together with his niece Sonya, has sacrificed his life managing the estate of Professor Serebryakov, his former brother-in-law and Sonya’s father. But when the Professor returns from the city with his glamorous young wife Yelena, tensions spiral as their world is thrown upside down. Chekhov’s tragicomic masterpiece of dashed dreams and thwarted and eternal love returns to the West End in Lev Dodin’s definitive interpretation of this classic play. Performed in Russian with English surtitles.',32,63);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(47,13,'Uncle Vanya','russian','3:15:00','Do not be surprised if they came to the theater. EVG. Vakhtangov for the play "Uncle Vanya", you will not recognize familiar characters, and famous words will sound unexpectedly. No, Rimas Tuminas did not commit an act of vandalism, he did not rewrite the text, did not shorten it. He sight-read it as if unaware that it was the interpreters. The Director cleared the stage from everyday life, leaving the battlefield of passions, broken illusions, unfulfilled hopes. Heroes of Chekhov, seen by Tuminas and embodied by the actors, live in the knocking of ambitions, philosophizing, diligence and laziness of service and consumption. In the works of A. P. Chekhov is the forerunner of the theater of the absurd: they say one thing, do another, think the third. "Uncle Vanya" Tuminas that Chekhov''s heroes think and what they admit only in moments of mental shock. They are sometimes tongue-tied, like uncle Vanya, or unnecessarily brutal as an Aster, but their confessions break out of the soul violently, like a man from a stuffy room to fresh air. The Director and the cast love their characters so different, lonely, sometimes funny. Yes, funny! Chekhov called his plays comedies. Directors and viewers wondered why these stories, filled with suffering, innuendo, always ending on a shrill-sad note — Comedy? For Tuminas Chekhov — the path of the search, the answer fact, the justification of the genre. Each of his production is closer to the meaning of this mysterious word Comedy, so contrary to the context of the story. It is hard not to recall the words of Pushkin: "the High Comedy is not based solely on laughter, but on the development of characters and often comes close to tragedy."',14,4);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(48,13,'Uncle Vanya','russian','2:55:00','Forty years after the release of the film "Uncle Vanya" with Innokenty Smoktunovsky starring Andrei Konchalovsky returned to Chekhov to rethink the topic of finding a man himself, his place in life and happiness. Fans of the poetic and melancholic film should take into account the fact that the new interpretation of the play with the film has nothing in common. The Director enters into polemics with himself, preferring at present to interpret the fate of the Russian intelligentsia in "Uncle Vanya" not as tragedy but as farce. According to the Director, the play is designed in classical aesthetics, but its interpretation is not classical. In the production, the main character is not boring, as is the case in Many Chekhov''s dramas: Konchalovsky is more concerned about feelings and destinies told without pathos. Perhaps that is why many critics agreed that although the play is not a discovery, but a revelation. A clear interpretation of the play by the Director, a strong acting ensemble (Julia Vysotskaya, Alexander Filippenko, Pavel Derevyanko, Alexander Domogarov and others), the design of the play by the artist Rustam Khamdamov — all this distinguishes the production on the Moscow stage.',16,3);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(49,14,'Three Sisters','russian','3:15:00','Critically acclaimed the world over, and winner of a Drama Desk Award, The Sovremennik’s Three Sisters is widely regarded as one of the seminal versions of Anton Chekhov’s classic tale, enthralling audiences from Paris to New York, Berlin to London. Rediscover the story of sisters Olga, Masha and Irina Prozorov in this mesmerising production, as they search for their meaning in the modern world and yearn for a life in Moscow away from their provincial home. With a succession of guests, family and lovers visiting their house, events unfold that will shape their destinies.',32,63);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(50,14,'Three Sisters','russian','3:10:00','The idea to restore, perhaps, the most legendary production of VL. Nemirovich-Danchenko appeared on the eve of the anniversary of Chekhov. Turning to the play of Chekhov, the people''s artist Of the USSR T. V. Doronina seems to offer the audience a wonderful atmosphere of the play, telling about the tragic fate of three women who dreamed, loved, suffered, but could not become happy...',13,3);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(51,14,'Three Sisters','russian','3:20:00','Sisters Prozorovs (Olga, Masha and Irina) yearn in one of the provincial towns of the Russian province, where at the time is a military garrison. Against the background of this immense provincial boredom unfolds the relationship of the middle of the sisters — Masha and officer Vershinin, younger — Irina and Baron Tuzenbach. Masha will never find her happiness, Irina will lose her beloved forever. Leave town regiment. The sounds of a military band will subside. Long, long days... "To Moscow, to Moscow!"— will remain the eternal symbol of dashed hopes all the heroes of this drama by A. P. Chekhov.',47,4);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(52,14,'Three Sisters','russian','3:25:00','We can safely say that the "three sisters" is a logical continuation and development of another production of Konchalovsky, "Uncle Vanya": it can be traced both in the story and in the same scenery and almost the same cast. The performance with Julia Vysotskaya, Alexander Domogarov, Irina Kartashova, Pavel Derevyanko, Larisa Kuznetsova and other artists from the previous production is the second part of a peculiar dilogy of Konchalovsky. The Director''s idea is that in the" Three sisters " roles of actors are changed to the opposite. The Director managed to achieve a complete reflection of the classical psychology of the Chekhov world. Monologues of this play is laced with sharp irony. Konchalovsky himself seems to take the place of a certain conductor who interprets the classical work in his own way. Seeing the play "Three sisters", you will be able to overestimate this work and completely from a new side to experience the personal tragedies of each of the main characters of the play.',16,5);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(53,14,'Three Sisters','russian','2:00:00','The play "Three sisters" is a sincere attempt to make the text of Chekhov''s play extremely alive, extremely modern, extremely natural. According to the Director, six months he and the actors parsed the text, studying it very carefully. With such a dive, all the symbolism of the" Three sisters " goes away, and reveals a detailed, subtle, absolutely reasonable psychological structure. This is what is interesting in the play. An interesting reality of the war in a provincial town is the very alive, specific, situational human manifestations: love, emotions, relations. In the play there is no symbolism, no abstraction, no philosophizing. This is an extremely specific, extremely household, and primarily household emotionally thing about living, ordinary people.',46,3);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(54,15,'Miracle of Saint Anthony','russian','1:45:00','Have you ever met people for whom their social status is more important than the truth itself and the essence of things? This is exactly what happens to the heirs of the owner of the countless riches of the deceased Hydrangea – people who seem educated and decent, causing universal respect and enjoying great authority among the inhabitants of their city. Nothing can prevent the funeral at a level worthy of their position in society, thereby casting a shadow on the well-known and respectable name. Removal of the body of his aunt turns for them in carefully planned to the smallest detail action, designed only to ensure that the rich clan spoke with breath and delight. And even standing side by side with St. Anthony, able to work miracles, a crack in the tile on the floor and the entry into the inheritance nephews are busy much more than the opportunity to bring back to life their dead aunt – the miracle of resurrection. What is human life worth compared to millions of banknotes, posh houses, trout with sauce and baked grouse?',17,4);
