INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(63,20,'Flight','russian','3:45:00','The most powerful performance on Bulgakov of recent years is about love, war, hunger and large doses of morphine. The play "Running" is a landmark work for Mikhail Bulgakov. E. S. Bulgakova recalled: "It was a favorite play of Mikhail Afanasievich. He loved this play as a mother loves a child."  The stage story of the play "Running" was not easy. After the ban in 1928, her rehearsals at the Moscow art Theater, the question of the production of "Running" four times considered at meetings of the Politburo. Second, after the "Days of Turbin," the emergence of white officers on the scene, the authorities did not allow. During the life of the author, the play was not staged, which "was almost a disaster for M. Bulgakov." The premiere of "running" took place only in 1957 in Stalingrad.',14,5);
