INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(98,31,'Woe from Wit','russian','3:00:00','The debut production on the Moscow stage of the leading actor of the troupe Alexander Yatsko, who has behind him directing experience. The play gives a "fresh" look at the work familiar from the school bench, while remaining faithful to the spirit of the great Comedy. Alexander Yatsko is convinced that "Woe from wit" is the best play ever written in Russian. He made textbook heroes alive modern people, whose thoughts and actions are close and clear to those sitting in the hall. The chamber atmosphere of the stage "under the roof" allows you to look at the faces of Griboedov''s characters in detail and in a new way, to understand the logic and motives of their behavior, and the stylish lapidary scenography, authored by the Director of the play, gives the action of the Comedy an exquisite beauty.',16,4);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(99,31,'Woe from Wit','russian','3:00:00','Comedy "Woe from wit" has always been the hallmark of the Maly theater. It played all the time, artists of all generations played one and sometimes two or three roles. And the Maly theater also opens its new season with the show of this performance. The production of Sergei Zhenovach for 15 years, it also changed many performers, but the play has not lost its liveliness, originality and sharpness. He lives with his audience and over time, combining innovation and healthy traditionalism. Every year the production goes on tour and everywhere meets the hottest response among the audience. The role of Famusov is still performed by people''s artist of the USSR Yuri Solomin. In the play, the music of A. S. Griboyedov, M. I. Glinka, A. S. Dargomyzhsky, S. V. Rakhmaninov sounds.',47,2);
