INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(118,38,'The Storm','russian','2:50:00','"The storm" is probably the most famous drama A. N. Ostrovsky. Many still consider it one of the most mysterious works of world drama. After its publication in 1859, after the first premieres in Moscow and St. Petersburg, the "Storm" immediately generated a lot of controversy and opposing judgments. Someone called it a frivolous farce, and someone-a perfect poetic creation. Someone thought that Ostrovsky expressed a radical protest against the outdated way of life, and someone, on the contrary, saw in his drama the apology of conservative Russian life. But all the people of the theater clearly felt in the" Storm " the mood of a global catastrophe, which is designed to either destroy the world, or update it. So huge was the impact of seemingly simple, in the modern view, the history that occurred in a certain provincial town of Kalinov on the Volga river. The main character of" Thunderstorm " Katerina - a young married woman-for the first time experiencing a strong love for a man who is not her husband. This feeling turns into a fatal test for her, because neither her upbringing nor the General way of life do not allow her to leave the family for the sake of her lover, who is also not ready to accept her...',14,4);
