INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(126,43,'The Minor','russian','2:20:00','"I don''t want to study, I want to get married!"— this exclamation of a sissy Mitrofanushka known to all. The play "the Minor" was written over two centuries ago, but it seems specifically designed to protect today''s youth from repeating Mitrofanushka errors. In early 1782, Fonvizin read to friends and secular acquaintances Comedy "Nedorosl", on which he worked for many years. In the "Ignoramus", just remark the first biographer Fonvizin, P. A. Vyazemsky, author of "not noisy, do not laugh, and angry at sin and condemns him without mercy, and laugh if the audience derived abuse and lollygagging, and then suggestible laughter entertains from the impressions deeper and more deplorable." There is a legend that after the premiere of" Nedorosl "in St. Petersburg Fonvizin approached Prince Potemkin and said:" Die, Denis, it is better not to write." According to another version, these words belong to Derzhavin, not Potemkin. The production of "Nedorosl" was associated with many difficulties. Having been refused in St. Petersburg, the playwright in may 1782 travels with actor I.Dmitrievsky to Moscow. But here he will fail: "the Moscow Russian theater censor", frightened by the courage of many replicas, does not miss the Comedy on stage. A few months later Fonvizin still managed to" break through " the production of Comedy: September 24, 1782 premiered in St. Petersburg, and may 14, 1783 — in Moscow, on the stage of the Medox theater. The success of "Nedorosl" in Moscow was huge. Soon it was put on stage by students of the University (as you know, on the basis of the University theater there was a Small).',47,3);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(127,44,'Boris Godunov','russian','3:20:00','Both wisdom and will are with Tsar Boris. However, led him to welcome the power of a bloody crime. Heavy payback... The time of troubles in Russia is inevitable. In this tragedy, Tolstoy raises the eternal question of power, its goals and means. And decides this question "in the light of Conscience."',47,3);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(128,45,'Little tragedies','russian','1:30:00','"Little tragedies" is the directorial debut of the people''s artist Vyacheslav Ezepov, who played three roles in this performance: Salieri, Baron and Chairman. Capacious, laconic, full of indescribable energy dramatic novels of the great Russian classic are the best suited for a small stage, where the conversation of the artist and the viewer takes place at the closest distance. Envy, jealousy, greed, the recklessness, the eternal evil of man, they wrote about Pushkin, about it also tells the little theatre in the production.',47,3);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(129,46,'Masquerade','russian','2:30:00','Masquerade is a theatre of characters, intrigues, flirting, intense and dangerous confessions of revelations. Clowns, cynics, hoaxer, clowns, mummers, romantic heroes are a succession of "without shame" protected Neznanskiy. Masquerade-a game with a partner, fate, here kill the word, gossip, then to remove the mask, to shed " bitter tears of compassion." What a fascinating and treacherous community this masquerade is. Mindlessly started to intrigue cluttered with details, speculation and rolling, like a snowball, the victim and the adversary. Masquerade is running in circles without stopping, without respite, his impetuous vortex pulls, bravura joy gives courage, and sometimes deprived of reason. Masquerade-a dream, the meaning of which opens with the last chord of the waltz.',14,3);
INSERT INTO [SPECTACLE INFO](spectacle_id, artwork_id, spectacle_name, language, duration, description, theater_id, age_restrictions_id) VALUES(130,46,'Masquerade','russian','3:00:00','To see Lermontov''s romantic play "Masquerade" on stage uncut and ruthless Director''s editing today is possible only in the Small theater. ... Perhaps nowhere in recent years has there been so many brilliant acting works, so many full-blooded, skillfully played characters in the "masquerade"... In the performance of a powerful actor''s ensemble, the play "masquerade" plays with faces, like a precious stone, which does not require additional cutting. Andrei Zhitinkin''s production combines the great style of the Imperial theatre with the asceticism of modern European theatre. ... The notorious old-fashioned for some, the preserved tradition for others-the old recipe, according to which in a Small "cherries" are harvested for more than one century, - consistently give as a result a highly professional masterful performance, at the head of which is the perfect word of the author',47,4);
